## Context
Reviewer 2 linear comments: jargon and acronyms used before definition. QUICK,
low-risk, mechanical — a good first deliverable. Write definitions concretely
(avoid new AI-tells per 0134).

## Actions — define at first occurrence
1. Rio markers (currently partially defined p8; first use earlier) — define at first mention.
2. DAC (Development Assistance Committee) — defined p13, used from p7; move definition to first use.
3. Concessional vs non-concessional flows, "grant element" (>=25%), face value vs subsidy content (p7) — explain concretely.
4. GNI target; GEF grants; CDM (how it works in practice, brief); Bali Action Plan; "Barnesian form" — define/gloss at first mention.

## Test
- Source-inspection check: each term's first textual occurrence is within N words of its definition (grep-based).

## Exit criteria
- [ ] Every term above defined at first use; no forward-reference definitions remain
